SuperSport United FC has on Thursday announced that Goalkeeper, Ronwen Williams has signed a new deal with the Club that will see him with the Pretoria side until 2022.SuperSport United CEO Stanley Matthews said This is the first time we have given a player a straight 5 year deal and Ronwen thoroughly deserves it.&#8220;Williams has worked his way through the ranks from the age of 12 putting in many years of hard work in our academy and now in our first team. In a day and age where player loyalty is a rare commodity we are delighted to reward him for his dedication and excellent performances at the club both on and off the field of play, he said.The team said that they scouted the Bafana Bafana international goalkeeper twice in 2004 at the Danone U12 tournament that was in Polokwane and at the Schools Winter Sports games in Pietermaritzburg.Williams came to join the Matsatsantsa academy in 2005 and was promoted to the first team in the 2011/2012 season at the age of 19. At that time he was one of the youngest players Playing for the PSL. The 25-year-old is fast approaching 200 games for SuperSport United and is currently the longest serving player at the club, said the Club in a statement.Williams has collected four trophies with the club, three Nedbank Cup trophies and a Telkom Knock-Out title.-TNA Reporter &nbsp;